Reality TV star, Bamike Olawunmi-Adenibuyan aka Bam Bam has said people shouldn’t give birth to children if they won’t invest in them. The former BBNaija ‘Double Wahala’ participant, who welcomed second child with fellow housemate-turned-husband, Teddy A explained populating the world with badly behaved children/humans was totally unjust. According to Bam Bam, when parents give birth to children and do not imbibe them with the right morals, these child end up as badly behaved humans who continue to perpetrate evil, causing havoc to the society.   Fireboy DML becomes popular phone ambassador     Social media comedienne Madam Social dies     I’ll relocate to Ghana if Atiku or Tinubu becomes…   The media personality advised that people should rather not procreate if they have no intention of inculcating the right set of values in their young. “Parents, it is absolutely unfair to give this world badly behaved children/humans causing pain and havoc in the society, if you will not invest in them, please don’t birth them,” Bam Bam tweeted.